- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The library uses automated techniques to improve the accuracy of linear regression models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The library involves generating a large pool of features and selecting a small set of meaningful features, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The library can be used for feature engineering and selection in computer vision tasks, such as image classification. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses a software library for feature engineering and selection, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
